Subject: Reports throwing error "Unexpected exception: Encountered error: "Sequence contains more than one matching element" while generating report"
Description:
Post upgrade to 11.6 Published report throw errors. They seem to work but with error.

Unexpected exception: Encountered error: "Sequence contains more than one matching element" while generating report. Report generation task failed.

Reports were deleted and then recreated but still happens.
Solution_Comment__c:
- Close all instances of NEA
- Make a backup of the Reports folder at STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITReports 
- Either rename or delete the Reports folder form the above location
- Start NEA
- Run the FMS Mercer Jobs group (do not try to publish the reports)
